Ademola Babalola, Ibadan Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State will on Thursday swear in 14 commissioners recently cleared by the State House of Assembly. The Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Mr. Taiwo Adisa told The PUNCH that the nominees who had been screened and found worthy would be sworn-in at the executive chamber, governor’s office. Adisa said, “Yes, I can confirm to you that their (commissioners) swearing-in holds on Thursday.” READ ALSO: Beasts of No Nation: How Ikeja cantonment soldiers shot man, stabbed another on hospital bed —Police The commissioner nominees comprise four former lawmakers in the state Assembly; Kehinde Ayoola (Forner Speaker), Adeniyi Farinto (former chairman, parliamentary caucus), Mrs Funmilayo Orisadeyi (the only female nominee) and Muyiwa Ojekunle. Others are Chief Bayo Lawal, Dr Bashir Bello, Prof Oyelowo Oyewo, Prof Dawud Sangodoyin, Mr. Olasunkanmi Olaleye and Mr Adeniyi Adebisi. The remaining commissioner nominees whose appointment were confirmed are Mr. Abiodun Abdulraheem, Mr Seun Asamu, Dr Wasiu Olatunbosun and Mr Akinola Ojo.